fd", "default": false, "description": "Category: An issue proposing an enhancement or a PR with one."}, {"id": 235137, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwyMzUxMzc=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-lint", "name": "A-lint", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: Lints (warnings about flaws in source code) such as unused_mut."}, {"id": 132910982, "node_id": "MDU6TGFiZWwxMzI5MTA5ODI=", "url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/labels/A-macros", "name": "A-macros", "color": "f7e101", "default": false, "description": "Area: All kinds of macros (custom derive, macro_rules!, proc macros, ..)"}], "state": "closed", "locked": false, "assignee": null, "assignees": [], "milestone": null, "comments": 3, "created_at": "2017-08-18T10:04:05Z", "updated_at": "2021-04-08T07:48:08Z", "closed_at": "2021-04-08T07:48:08Z", "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR", "active_lock_reason": null, "body": "On Nightly, rustc is generating `warning: doc comment not used by rustdoc` for macro expansions from outside the current crate.\r\n\r\n```\r\nwarning: doc comment not used by rustdoc\r\n  --> src/main.rs:12:5\r\n   |\r\n12 | /     error_chain!{\r\n13 | |         foreign_links {\r\n14 | |             Serde(::serde_json::Error);\r\n15 | |         }\r\n16 | |     }\r\n   | |_____^\r\n   |\r\n   = note: #[warn(unused_doc_comment)] on by default\r\n   = note: this error originates in a macro outside of the current crate\r\n```\r\n\r\nA reproducible example is available at https://github.com/bradfier/external-docstrings-example\r\n\r\nSince this behaviour isn't present on Stable, I'm assuming it's unintentional, if it's a new lint, or the semantics of when it is displayed have changed for Nightly, it would be useful if the warning message provided some more information about exactly where the lint is being triggered. At the moment, the produced info isn't much use for finding where the unused doc comment is.", "closed_by": {"login": "bradfier", "id": 3495954, "node_id": "MDQ6VXNlcjM0OTU5NTQ=", "avatar_url": "https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3495954?v=4", "gravatar_id": "", "url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier", "html_url": "https://github.com/bradfier", "followers_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/followers", "following_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/following{/other_user}", "gists_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/gists{/gist_id}", "starred_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/starred{/owner}{/repo}", "subscriptions_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/subscriptions", "organizations_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/orgs", "repos_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/repos", "events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/events{/privacy}", "received_events_url": "https://api.github.com/users/bradfier/received_events", "type": "User", "site_admin": false}, "reactions": {"url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/43974/reactions", "total_count": 1, "+1": 1, "-1": 0, "laugh": 0, "hooray": 0, "confused": 0, "heart": 0, "rocket": 0, "eyes": 0}, "timeline_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/rust-lang/rust/issues/43974/timeline", "performed_via_github_app": null, "state_reason": "completed"}